[159:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'thumb will definitely be aligned with the z-axis, which is good. Now, we just have to verify if both fingers and thumb rotate in the same direction, and that seems to be the case. If your finger is curling in and'

[159:37] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'your thumb is curling out, then you have a problem and you\'ll have to go back to edit mode and roll this bone 180°. My bone is fine, so I\'ll just cancel'

[159:49] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'here, and I can keep working on the mechanism. To better focus on the hand, let\'s select all finger bones, all palm bones, press M and create a new collection,'

[160:01] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'call it hand, and I\'ll start it so that I only see the hand bones. So, for the mechanism, as we saw in the demo, we\'re going to want a special'

[160:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'control bone aligned with the length of the finger. We can create it by copying the base of the finger, and with individual origins, let\'s scale this bone up so that it has the'

[160:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
