[211:39] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'reason. I was very careful with my actions and I have no idea why this happened. So, I assume it\'s some sort of stupid Blender behavior. So, let\'s select these bones and press M and move them to the bones collection where they'

[211:53] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'belong. Okay, since the bones on this collection will now become my deforming bones, I want to rename them with a special DEF prefix. And this is why earlier we'

[212:06] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'checked for 001 suffixes. We made sure that we didn\'t have any 001s and therefore, when we duplicated these bones, all of them got the exact 001 suffix. We can use that to our advantage'

[212:20] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'now. I\'m going to select all of these bones, go to edit batch rename, switch to bones, I\'ll choose set name, prefix,'

[212:33] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'I\'ll type DEF- and press okay. Now, these bones have the unique DEF- prefix, which means that we can easily get rid of the 001 suffix by just doing another battery name.'

[212:48] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Let\'s do find replace now. Find {dot} 001, replace with nothing, and press okay. Now, all of these bones will have the'

[213:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
