[227:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'see the benefits. The more complex a rig gets, the more important organization becomes. So, in this video, we are focusing on organizing our bones into collections. In the previous video, we took an'

[227:54] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'important step toward better organization by separating the deform bones into their own DEF collection. And as we discussed in level two, the three main types of bones in a rig are deform'

[228:08] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'd e f bones, mechanism m c h bones, and control bones. So, here is the plan for organizing our collections. First, we\'ll separate the non-deforming bones into m'

[228:20] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'c h and control collections. Then, we\'ll break the controls into smaller sub-collections, giving us full control over what we see while animating.'

