[232:44] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Everything that is not DEF or MCH is control. So, let\'s simplify the names and move them to the control collection. Again, I can remove unused.'

[232:58] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Next, we have the hand bones. So, here we have the main finger controls. They are controls, so move them to CTRL. Next, connective.'

[233:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'And these are the bones that we use as a connection between the deforming bones and the rest of the rig. A quick note here, you should be careful to keep these connective bones exactly as they'

[233:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'are, so do not tweak their positions and so on, because tweaking them may have an effect on the connection between deforming bones and the rest of the rig. So, we could even consider these bones'

[233:37] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'as a special type of bone and give them a special prefix, but I don\'t find that that useful. So, again, we\'ll just check these bones and see which of them are MCH and which need to be controls.'

[233:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'So, the neck head and the first three spine bones and the shoulders were all meant to be used as controls.'

[234:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'So, select them and move them to CTRL. The twist bones are not meant to be animated manually. So, select them'

[234:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'and move them to MCH. And let\'s do this for the leg twists as well. This hand bone will also not be animated'

[234:28] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'directly because we are either animating the FK hand or the IK hand. So, this is an MCH bone. Move it to MCH. The palms and fingers can be used for'

[234:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'controls. So, move them to CTRL. These big arm bones are already named MCH. That also includes the hand because'

[234:53] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'again the arm is either controlled by the IK or FK and not by these intermediate bones. So, let\'s move them to MCH. The fingers will be controls. Move them'

[235:06] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to CTRL. The pelvis and first spine are not controls. We are controlling this part of the body with the inverted bones that we created.'

[235:19] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'So, let\'s select these bones and move them to MCH. And these foot and toe are also intermediate or MCH bones. What we actually use to animate the foot and toe'

[235:33] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'are the IK and FK foot bones. So, let\'s move these to MCH. And remove unused. And now we are just left with deforming, MCH and control'

[235:45] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'bones. Nice. Now, I\'m going to take a look at the MCH bones, and I mainly want to check their names. I want to make sure that all bones on this collection are actually'

[235:57] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'named MCH. There are quite a lot of bones, and they are overlapping.'

[236:10] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'So, working here can be a little bit difficult, but here is what we can do. I\'ll disable these names. And in the outliner, go to search and type MCH-'

[236:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'This will display all MCH bones in the outliner. And now I can just control-click on them, and that will select them. Ignore the vertex groups. We just want'

[236:44] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the bones. Once you have all of these MCH- bones selected, press H to hide them. And now, what we have left is all bones that need to be MCH, but don\'t have the prefix yet. So, select all of them, go'

[236:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to edit batch rename, switch to bones, set name prefix MCH- Press okay, and that\'s it.'

[237:09] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Okay, now we can focus on the controls and split them into nice and easy-to-understand collections. Organizing the controls will be'

[237:21] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
