[253:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'I\'ll use the curvy shape similar to what we did in level two. But here\'s an important difference and an important new technique that I want to share with you.'

[253:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'I want this shape to be up here in the chest area. So of course I can use the transformation to move it up here and initially it looks fine, but if I actually use this control, you\'ll see that it kind of becomes disconnected'

[253:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'from the actual geometry. Blender has an amazing tool to fix just that and that is this override transform option. In here I can enter another bone and the shape will then appear at the position'

[253:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'of that bone. So I kind of want this shape to appear at the position of this chest bone. So if I just press F2 and copy its name, then go to the shape'

[254:09] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'and paste it here and select it, the shape will now offset a bit. That\'s because I have some custom values here. So let\'s set Y to zero and now it just automatically appears exactly here at the chest and when I rotate this'

[254:22] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'control, it looks just right. It sticks to the chest of the character perfectly. So now I can tweak it a bit with the usual tools. And it looks great.'

[254:39] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'So let\'s do the same for the hips control. I want it to appear at the hips two bone. So copy the name, select the main hips control and let\'s set override transforms to hips'

[254:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'two. Then just tweak the size and the position of this bone slightly. And it\'s done. Okay, great.'

[255:10] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
