[261:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Now you can play with the rig and check'

[261:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'if the shapes feel right. If not, make adjustments. The shapes are looking good to me. So,'

[262:10] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'next step, of course, is to also set bone colors. Now, here is an additional step you can take when setting up the pose bone colors. These presets have a specific color for the default color of the bone,'

[262:23] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'for the color when it\'s selected, and for the color when it\'s active. And these three colors are very similar. So, something that many Blender users like to to is to unify the selected and active'

[262:35] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'color of the bones, meaning that the shapes will have a specific color only when they\'re not selected at all. And when they\'re active and selected, they\'ll have a unified bluish color.'

[262:48] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'We can do that by going to edit preferences, themes, and expand bone color sets. And these are the presets that we get here.'

[263:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
